            <h1 style="padding-bottom: 15px;"><i>―   COOKIE POLICY   ―</i></h1>
            <ol type="I">
                <p>We use cookies or similar tools on our website to improve its performance and your experience. This policy explains how we do it.</p>
                <li>What is a cookie?</li>
                <p>A cookie is a small file consisting of a textual set of information that a website sends to a visitor\'s computer or other Internet-connected device. Cookies perform certain functions (including distinguishing you from other users on the same website or storing certain information related to you, such as your preferences) and are used by most sites to facilitate your browsing.</p>
                <li>The types of cookies we use:</li>
                <ul>
                    <li>Functional cookies</li>
                    <p>We use cookies that allow the website to store your actions and preferences for a certain period of time so that you do not have to enter them every time you visit the site or move from one page to another. These cookies do not store personal information.</p>
                    <li>Analytical cookies</li>
                    <p>Thanks to these cookies, we monitor the traffic to our site and can analyze how easily our users use it (Google Analytics cookies). These cookies do not store personal information. They show us which pages on our site you viewed, whether you visited our site through a mobile or desktop device and other anonymous data.</p>
                    <li>Precision targeting cookies</li>
                    <p>These cookies contain information about how you have used our site and may be triggered by our advertising partners. These cookies do not store personal information. Thanks to them, you will not be shown information that is irrelevant to you. These are dynamic cookies on Facebook, Google, Adform, Adwise and more.</p>
                </ul>
                <li>How do I delete or block cookies?</li>
                <p>You can control and / or delete cookies whenever you like - visit aboutcookies.org for more information. You can delete all cookies already stored on your computer, and you can also set most browsers to block them. However, if you do this, you may need to manually adjust some parameters each time you visit our site, and some services and features may not work.</p>
            </ol>
