                <li>How long do we process your personal data?</li>
                <p>Information that may contain personal information and be stored for no longer than is necessary for the purposes for which the data were collected and processed. If, at a later stage, your personal data are related to the conclusion and / or performance of a contract between us, they will be processed for the duration of the contract and until the expiry of the statutory time limits for bringing a claim. The purpose is to protect our common rights and legitimate interests in the event of a possible legal dispute. Commercial and accounting information is stored for a period of 10 years in compliance with the special requirements of the law.</p>
                <li>Do we make automated decision-making and profiling??</li>
                <p>Max Graphic EOOD. does not perform automated decision-making against you, which has legal consequences based solely on automated processing of personal data and / or profiling. Max Graphic EOOD. does not currently profile the users of the site.</p>
                <li>What rights do you have regarding the processing of your personal data?</li>
                <p>Right of access<br> You have the right to request information whether we process personal data related to you.</p>
                <p>Right of correction<br> You have the right to request that your personal data be corrected if any changes have been made to them or found to be incomplete or inaccurate.</p>
                <p>Right of erasure (\"right to be forgotten\")<br> You have the right to request that your personal data be deleted when it is no longer needed for the purposes for which it was collected and processed, if the reason for processing your personal data is gone and there is no other legal basis; if your personal data is to be erased to comply with a legal obligation.</p>
                <p>After considering all the circumstances of this request, we may refuse to delete your personal data if the processing is necessary to comply with our obligation under a law, a public interest task, or in the exercise and defense of legal claims.</p>
                <p>The exercise of the right of erasure may not affect the rights and freedoms of others.</p>
                <p>Right to restrict processing<br> You have the right to request a restriction on processing while we review your request, which challenges the accuracy of your personal data. You may request a restriction on processing when you do not want your personal data deleted in connection with the exercise or protection of legal claims. Processing restriction may also apply to your objection to automatic decision-making against you or profiling.</p>
                <p>Right to portability<br> You have the right to receive personal data that concerns you and that you have provided to us in a structured, widely used and machine-readable format, and you have the right to request that we transfer this data to another administrator in the following cases:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Contract-based processing and automated processing: In the exercise of this right, the transfer can be made by us to another administrator only when technically feasible.This right does not apply to processing required to perform a task by public interest. The exercise of the right of portability may not affect the rights and freedoms of others.</li>
                    <li>Right to object to automated decision-making against you: When decisions are made against you, solely on the basis of automated processing of your personal data, including when profiling, you have the right to object. This right may not be exercised when automated processing is necessary for the conclusion or performance of a contract between us.</li>
                    <li>Right to complain: If you believe that your data protection rights have been violated, you can file a complaint with us. You can also file a complaint with the Commission for Personal Data Protection, Sofia 1592, 2 Tsvetan Lazarov Blvd., tel: +359 2 9153 518, e-mail: kzld@cpdp.bg</li>
                </ul>
